# Significant Changes Summary — Scrinium

## v0.1.0 → v0.2.0 (2026-07-06 → 2026-07-07)

### Architecture & Integration

| Change | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| **Shared ChromaDB** | Scrinium now uses the same ChromaDB collection as docling-search, enabling cross-tool document access |
| **Unified document collection** | Single `scrinium` collection for all sources — web uploads and MCP tools share the same data |
| **Shared embedder** | Both Scrinium and docling-search use `jina-embeddings-v3` via fastembed from the same backend |
| **Metadata alignment** | Metadata format standardized to `doc_name` + `header` across all components |

### Improvements

| Change | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| **Upload stability** | No timeout on uploads, abort support, OOM handling, graceful browser-sleep recovery |
| **Real progress tracking** | XHR-based upload progress bar + conversion status feedback |
| **Cache busting** | HTML templates served with cache-control headers and cache-busting |
| **Logging** | Structured logging added throughout for debugging |
| **Timeout increase** | Docling conversion timeout raised to 60 minutes for large PDFs |

### The Stack (as documented)

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                   User (Browser)                 │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│              Scrinium (FastAPI)                  │
│  - Web UI (upload + chat)                       │
│  - REST API (documents + sessions)              │
│  - JWT authentication                           │
├──────────────────┬──────────────────────────────┤
│  docling-mcp     │   docling-search             │
│  (PDF→Markdown)  │   (semantic search)          │
├──────────────────┴──────────────────────────────┤
│              ChromaDB + jina-embeddings-v3       │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```
